  "prompt": "How do you enroll to the Rakuten Institute of Technology?",
  "response": "The **Rakuten Institute of Technology (RIT)** is Rakuten's research and development organization, focused on innovation and technology. However, it is not a traditional educational institution where you can enroll as a student. Instead, RIT primarily employs researchers, engineers, and professionals who work on cutting-edge projects in areas such as AI, blockchain, data science, and more.\n\nIf you are interested in joining the Rakuten Institute of Technology, here\u2019s how you can proceed:\n\n1. **Visit the Rakuten Careers Page**  \n   - Go to the official Rakuten careers website: [Rakuten Careers](https://global.rakuten.com/corp/careers/).  \n   - Search for job openings at the Rakuten Institute of Technology.  \n   - Look for positions that match your skills and expertise, such as research, engineering, or data science roles.\n\n2. **Apply for a Position**  \n   - Submit your application, including your resume/CV and any other required materials.  \n   - Highlight your technical skills, research experience, and any relevant projects.\n\n3. **Prepare for the Interview Process**  \n   - If selected, you\u2019ll go through an interview process, which may include technical assessments and discussions about your background and expertise.  \n   - Be prepared to demonstrate your knowledge in your field of study or work.\n\n4. **Networking**  \n   - Connect with current or former RIT employees on platforms like LinkedIn to learn more about the work environment and projects.  \n   - Attend industry conferences or events where Rakuten or RIT representatives might be present.\n\nKeep in mind that RIT does not offer formal enrollment or academic programs. Instead, it is a workplace for professionals contributing to Rakuten's technological advancements.\n\nIf you are looking for educational opportunities, you may consider Rakuten\u2019s partnerships with universities or other initiatives like the **Rakuten Gora Campus**, which offers training programs for employees. However, these are typically internal programs for Rakuten staff. \n\nLet me know if you'd like further guidance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
